Racial tensions erupted in Toledo, Ohio when white supremacists clashed with counter-protestors, leading to rioting in an impoverished neighborhood.
Holocaust survivors commemorated the 6 million Jews killed by Nazis, while white supremacists faced off with angry crowds outside Faneuil Hall.
A city council candidate withdrew after posting on a white supremacist forum, sparking controversy.
Amidst the chaos, a black man retaliated against a white woman, reflecting deep-seated hatred.
The situation escalated as gang members looted and burned buildings, prompting Mayor Jack Ford to intervene.
The aftermath left the community reeling, with calls for unity and understanding.
